The paper deals with the Frechet distance problem, which is a fundamental problem in computational geometry and has applications in GIS and map matching. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also presents a data structure and algorithms for solving variants of the Frechet distance problem efficiently, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also mentions the use of the Frechet distance problem in map matching, which is a problem in cs.DB (Databases). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of the Frechet distance problem in AI applications, such as finding the minimum Frechet distance between a point set and a polygonal curve, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper mentions the use of the Frechet distance problem in the context of simple polygons, which falls under cs.GR (Graphics).
